etty clear-cut class that inspires you in many ways.", "helpful": 0, "not_helpful": 4, "tags": []}]}, {"professor_id": "1485192", "professor_name": "Brenda Davison", "avg_rating": 5.0, "avg_difficulty": 4.0, "review_count": 1, "reviews": [{"rating": 5.0, "difficulty": 4.0, "course_code": "150", "date": "Nov 29th, 2014", "metadata": {"For Credit": "Yes", "Attendance": "Not Mandatory", "Would Take Again": "", "Grade": "", "Textbook": "Yes"}, "review_msg": "Math-150 was the first ever course I've taken at SFU and Brenda made a pretty good impression right from the get go. The course material is hard and somewhat confusing at times, she's always willing to help out students during  workshop hours and even after lectures. After asking her a question, you'll be thinking \"why didn't I think of that.\"", "helpful": 0, "not_helpful": 0, "tags": []}]}, {"professor_id": "1026175", "professor_name": "Jamie Mulholland", "avg_rating": 5.0, "avg_difficulty": 3.0, "review_count": 2, "reviews": [{"rating": 5.0, "difficulty": 3.0, "course_code": "150", "date": "Dec 10th, 2024", "metadata": {"For Credit": "Yes", "Attendance": "Mandatory", "Would Take Again": "Yes", "Grade": "C+", "Textbook": "N/A"}, "review_msg": "Overall, an amazing professor, his video lectures are absolutely amazing and really easy to understand. His midterms and finals can be challenging, if you haven't taken calculus before, but he provides you will lots of practice midterms/finals. His web assign/seminar assignments are also free marks.", "helpful": 0, "not_helpful": 0, "tags": ["Amazing lectures ", "Gives good feedback", "Respected"]}, {"rating": 5.0, "difficulty": 3.0, "course_code": "150", "date": "May 23rd, 2015", "metadata": {"For Credit": "Yes", "Attendance": "Not Mandatory", "Would Take Again": "", "Grade": "A", "Textbook": "Yes"}, "review_msg": "Awesome professor. Puts a lot of effort into teaching. Lectures are very well organized. Uses interactive examples. Math can be boring sometimes, but not when he's teaching it. Best prof so far.", "helpful": 3, "not_helpful": 11, "tags": []}]}, {"professor_id": "1463517", "professor_name": "Zhaosong LU", "avg_rating": 3.5, "avg_difficulty": 3.0, "review_count": 1, "reviews": [{"rating": 3.5, "difficulty": 3.0, "course_code": "150", "date": "Jul 30th, 2015", "metadata": {"For Credit": "Yes", "Attendance": "", "Would Take Again": "", "Grade": "", "Textbook": "No"}, "review_msg": "At first was difficult to understand through in accent but got used to after a week or two. He dumbs down his lectures a lot going through every single step he does and repeating points multiple times. Personally I liked this, made what he was teaching very clear and easy to follow.", "helpful": 1, "not_helpful": 0, "tags": []}]}, {"professor_id": "10716", "professor_name": "Andy Heard", "avg_rating": 4.0, "avg_difficulty": 2.0, "review_count": 1, "reviews": [{"rating": 4.0, "difficulty": 2.0, "course_code": "150", "date": "Apr 5th, 2002", "metadata": {"For Credit": "", "Attendance": "", "Would Take Again": "", "Grade": "", "Textbook": ""}, "review_msg": "easy class...nice guy", "helpful": 0, "not_helpful": 0, "tags": []}]}, {"professor_id": "58167", "professor_name": "Lakshman (Lucky) One", "avg_rating": 3.17, "avg_difficulty": 3.0, "review_count": 3, "reviews": [{"rating": 4.5, "difficulty": 3.0, "course_code": "150", "date": "Dec 9th, 2002", "metadata": {"For Credit": "", "Attendance": "", "Would Take Again": "", "Grade": "", "Textbook": ""}, "review_msg": "He's one of the best profs", "helpful": 0, "not_helpful": 0, "tags": []}, {"rating": 1.0, "difficulty": 5.0, "course_code": "150", "date": "Nov 14th, 2002", "metadata": {"For Credit": "", "Attendance": "", "Would Take Again": "", "Grade": "", "Textbook": ""}, "review_msg": "if you're not an engineering major, he makes you feel like you're a nobody", "helpful": 0, "not_helpful": 0, "tags": []}, {"rating": 4.0, "difficulty": 1.0, "course_code": "150", "date": "Oct 25th, 2002", "metadata": {"For 